			array('Tier'=>'Quirk','Direction'=>'quirk','Description'=>'The smallest tier of Hitches, are called Quirks and are intended for subtle characterization, and annoying nuisances. Quirks may have a Boon no greater than Half the Character’s Facet Boon','Gnarls'=>1), //0
			array('Tier'=>'Flaw','Direction'=>'flaw','Description'=>'The middle tier of Hitches, are called Flaws and are intended to be profoundly afflicting for the Characters that have them, representing things the Character should want to change about themselves, their imperfections, biases and phobias amongst other things.  Flaws may be no bigger than the Character’s Facet Boon.','Gnarls'=>2), //1
			array('Tier'=>'Woe','Direction'=>'woe','Description'=>'The greatest tier of Hitches are the devastating Woes. Woes have Banes higher than the Character’s own Facet Boons, seemingly creating additional suffering from nothing. It is perhaps because of this that Woes usually attract the Increated. The Increated, who lurk forever just beyond the imagination, once they spot a Woe Trigger a few times will swoop in to swap all the Sway generated by a Woe being triggered with Twists. These Twisted Woes allow Characters to generate Twists and store them on their Hitches, creating Twisted Facets, but can disable a character when triggered. Woes can be at most Boon 40 for most Characters and Twisted Woes can never be larger than Boon 82.','Gnarls'=>3),//2
			array('Tier'=>'Resolved (Persona)','Direction'=>'persona','Description'=>'The Hitch is Resolved and instead the Character may claim an additional Persona. This additional Persona will grant the Character a new way of gaining Chi and may add new Goals.','Gnarls'=>0),//3
